<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600, GMT July 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Former Indonesian President Soeharto has suffered a
mild stroke and would remain in hospital for the next one to two
weeks, the chief of the Pertamina Hospital where Soeharto has been
admitted said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"His treatment would take one to two weeks," Sudjono
Hartoadmodjo said at a press briefing here. (Indonesia-Soeharto-
Stroke)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- French President Jacques Chirac left here on Wednesday
for Africa on a five-day visit that will take him to four
countries, his seventh trip to the black continent since he became
president in 1995. (France-Africa-Chirac)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The wreckage of John F. Kennedy Jr.'s small plane
was located Wednesday, with Kennedy's body still aboard, off the
coast of Martha's Vineyard in the Massachusetts State of the
United States, senior government sources said. (US-Kennedy-Remains)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korea and the International Monetary Fund (IMF)
have foreseen a 6 percent to 7 percent growth in the South Korean
economy this year, compared with the previous estimate of 2
percent.
</P>
<P>
They also predicted that the economy will grow by 5 to 6
percent the next year.
</P>
<P>
The forecast came at a two-week semiannual consultation meeting
between Seoul and the IMF, which started on July 6, said the
Finance and Economy Ministry Wednesday. (SKorea-IMF) 
</P>
</TEXT>
