<HEADLINE> Pakistan Reiterates "One China" Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government
Wednesday reiterated its "one China" policy, saying Taiwan is an
inalienable part of China.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan has always believed that there is only one China and
the government of the People's Republic of China is the sole
representative of the Chinese people, said a Foreign Office press
release here.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese sovereignty and territory are indivisible and
Taiwan must be reunited with the motherland, it added.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan fully supports the stand taken by the Chinese
government, which has reacted justifiably to Lee Teng-hui's recent
statement, it concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
