<HEADLINE> Etxebarria Wins His Second Stage of the Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRISE, July 21 (Xinhua) -- David Etxebarria of Spain took his
second win in five day as he stage victory in five days when he
won the 16th stage in Pau of France on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The final day in the Pyrenees ended with the Spanish rider
outsprinting Colombian Carlos Contreras with Italian Alberto Elli
third in the 192 kms leg from Lannemezan.
</P>
<P>
The leading group of 12 split over the final kilometres leaving
six riders to battle out the finish.
</P>
<P>
American Lance Armstrong retained his overall leader's yellow
jersey after finishing 21 seconds behind Etxebarria.
</P>
<P>
It was Spain's second successive stage triumph and third in
five days. Tuesday's winner, Fernando Escartin, remained six
minutes and 15 seconds behind Armstrong in the overall standings.
</P>
</TEXT>
