<HEADLINE> 885 People Killed in Guerrilla Conflicts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Altogether 885 people have been
killed in Nepal in the conflicts between police and the ultra-left
guerrillas since the outbreak of the guerrilla activities three
and half years ago.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Home Purna Bahadur Khadka informed the House of
Representatives Wednesday that a total of 75 security personnel,
153 civilians and 657 guerrilla members have been killed in the
conflicts during the period.
</P>
<P>
Khadka added that property worth of more than Rs. 90 million
(about 1.3 million U.S. dollars) has been damaged due to the
guerrilla activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
