<HEADLINE> Pakistan Condemns Murder of 35 Innocent Kashmiris </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Foreign Office
Spokesman Tariq Altaf Wednesday condemned the mass murder of 35
innocent Kashmiris, including women and children, by the Indian
armed forces in India-held Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
The entire village of Thatri in Doda district has been put
under military siege, Altaf said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The press release recalled that only recently a total of 32
people were killed in different areas in India-held Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
"These murders in cold-blood are a proof of India's brutal
repression of the Kashmiris who are carrying on their indigenous
struggle for their right to self determination," said Altaf.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman noted that India is embarked on a policy of
ethnic cleansing. "In this day and age such abhorrent policies are
unacceptable to the international community," he added.
</P>
<P>
India should be prevented from carrying on with this policy of
ethnic cleansing, said the spokesman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
