<HEADLINE> African Youth Urged to Involve in Conflict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A senior Ethiopian official
Wednesday appealed African youth to serve as one of the major
building blocks in the search for effective mechanisms to bring
sustainable peace in the continent.
</P>
<P>
The youth has a pivotal role to play in conflict prevention,
resolution and post-conflict reconstruction, Ethiopian Labor and
Social Affairs Minister Hassen Abdella said at a three-day
conference titled "Role of African Youth on Conflict Prevention
and Resolution".
</P>
<P>
"The challenge ahead lies in identifying measures for
strengthening the capacity of African youth to play an active role
in peace making and foster complementary efforts for peace among
the youth organizations of the continent," Hassen said.
</P>
<P>
Africans have to redouble their effort to resolve their
political and economic problems, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from most of African countries are attending
the three- day conference, which, informed sources said, would
establish an African youth peace council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
