<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Clothing Workers Get 30% Wage Hike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's clothing industry
workers have been awarded a 30 percent salary increment with
effect from this month, an industrial official said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Secretary-General of the National Union of the Clothing
Industry Freddy Mpofu said the increase followed successful
negotiations between the union and the employers.
</P>
<P>
He said the negotiating parties had also agreed that workers
would be awarded a further six percent increment in February next
year.
</P>
<P>
"Although we agreed on this percentage that does not mean that
it will offset the prevailing inflationary cost of living as the
prices of basic commodities keep on rising," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that workers realized during the negotiations that
employers were also facing viability problems.
</P>
<P>
Problems faced by the clothing industry had resulted in massive
 retrenchments which saw the number of employees in the sector
dropping from 26,000 to 19,500 since last October, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
