<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Rand Firm Against Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The South African rand ended
firmer against the U.S. dollar, but lost one percent against the
euro Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The rand ended at 6.1120 per dollar from a previous close of
6.1200, while against the euro the rand was closed at 6.4109 from
Tuesday's 6.3480.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market had been quiet and that the rand looked
to be stuck in a tight range around 6.1200 per dollar for most of
the day, but in the late afternoon, dollar sales had helped the
rand to strengthen below 6. 1200.
</P>
<P>
The recovery of the euro against the dollar, however, had led
to the rand losing one percent of its value against the euro.
</P>
</TEXT>
