<HEADLINE> 11 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Eleven rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) have been killed in recent military
operations staged by the Turkish security forces in southeastern
Turkey, an official statement said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule, said that the security forces had killed 10 PKK militants in
the rural area in Hizan town of Bitlis province and one in Tunceli
province.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a group of PKK rebels opened fire Tuesday night at a
police car on patrol at Yeni Mahalle Dikmen street in Bingol
province, killing two policemen, according to the semi-official
Anatolia News Agency on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a separatist war for an independent
Kurdish state in southeastern Turkey, which has claimed over
37,000 lives in the conflicts between the Turkish security forces
and the PKK militants since 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
