<HEADLINE> Syria Denies Involvement With Palestinian Factions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- A Syrian official said on
Wednesday that his country has nothing to do with the Palestinian
factions residing in Syria, the Syrian Arab News Agency (SANA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
The statement came in response to local press reports that the
Syrian government intends to ban the armed struggle of the
Palestinian factions in Syria against Israel.
</P>
<P>
The official, whose name was not disclosed, said Syria
interferes neither in the activities of the Palestinian
organizations nor in their decisions on their national legitimate
rights.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian factions and organizations residing in Syria
play their political role according to their vision in the
interest of the just cause of the Palestinian people, he added.
</P>
<P>
There are 10 Damascus-based radical Palestinian Islamic
factions that are opposed to the 1993 Oslo Accords between Israel
and the Palestine Liberation Organization led by Yasser Arafat.
</P>
<P>
Most prominent among such factions are the Hamas movement, the
People's Front for Palestine Liberation, the Democratic Front for
Palestine Liberation and the Jihad (holy war) movement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
