<HEADLINE> Russia, Belarus Ponder Unified Air Defense System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Russia and Belarus plan to create a
single regional air-defense system, the Interfax news agency
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Quoting sources in the Russian Defense Ministry, Interfax said
a Russian air force delegation flew to Minsk Wednesday for
consultations on the issue.
</P>
<P>
This new system is believed to be more integrated than the air
defense system of the Commonwealth of Independent States.
</P>
<P>
The Russian delegation, led by Deputy Commander
Lieutenant-General Yuri Bondarev, will stay in Minsk until
Saturday. The two sides will also discuss Belarussian air defense
units' participation in the Combat Cooperation '99 exercises to be
held on the Ashuluk training ground in the Astrakhan region on
August 23 to 27, Interfax said. 
</P>
