<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada to Exempt Visa for UAE Citizens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Canada is to exempt visa for
visitors from The United Arab Emirates (UAE), Canadian Ambassador
Stuart Modowall said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Negotiations for such an agreement is in an advanced stage
and could be finalized soon," the Canadian Ambassador told the the
UAE's official WAM news agency.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador, who is due to complete his tenure in the UAE
soon, said that the accord, when signed, will enable all UAE
nationals to travel to Canada without a visa, and they can stay in
Canada for a maximum of up to six months on each visit.
</P>
<P>
In return, Canadian citizens will be able to obtain entry visas
to travel to the UAE, with a validity of up to ten years and a
maximum stay of three months during each visit.
</P>
<P>
The UAE will be the second country in the Gulf and one of the
few countries worldwide to have such an accord with Canada, the
envoy said. Canada already has a mutual visa exemption agreement
with Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Modowall said that all efforts were being made to encourage
more travel by citizens of both countries. The growth in trade and
economic relations also indicates the potential for increased
movement between the two countries, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
