<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Urges Its People to Defend Territorial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The ruling Ethiopian People's
Revolutionary Democratic Front Wednesday called on the people of
the whole country to remain committed to national defense efforts.
</P>
<P>
The ruling party said in a statement that Ethiopia accepts the
framework agreement put forward by the Organization of African
Unity (OAU) and the modalities for the implementation of the
agreement because they are consistent with the party's principle.
</P>
<P>
The OAU framework agreement on the settlement of the conflict
between Ethiopia and Eritrea calls for the withdrawal of Eritrean
troops from all occupied Ethiopian territories.
</P>
<P>
The 35th OAU Summit convened in Algiers from July 12 to 14,
1999 also endorsed modalities from the implementation of the OAU
framework.
</P>
<P>
The modalities call for the return to the status quo ante that
had prevailed until May 6, 1998, which witnessed the breakout of
the Ethio- Eritrean war.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian defense forces should preserve their resolve to
defend the sovereignty and territorial integrity of the country,
the statement said.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, the Council of Ethiopian Ministers also pledged to
implement the OAU framework agreement and to continue seeking a
peaceful resolution to its dispute with Eritrea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
