<HEADLINE> Arafat, Aznar Urge Israel to Implement Wye </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GAZA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat and
Spanish Prime Minister Jose Maria Aznar here on Wednesday urged
Israel to immediately carry out the Wye River Memorandum.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a joint conference with Aznar, who was here on a
one-day visit to the Palestinian self-rule area, Arafat also
called on the United States, Europe and the international
community to exert efforts to help revive the Middle East peace
process.
</P>
<P>
Arafat stressed that Israel should immediately and faithfully
carry out all agreements between the two sides, particularly the
United States-brokered interim Wye agreement, which stipulates
that Israel should withdraw from 13.1 percent of the West Bank in
three phases.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Aznar also stressed the need for Israel to
implement all agreements, signed in the spirit of the
land-for-peace principle and the United Nations 242, 338
resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Aznar repledged his support for the Palestinian people's
legitimate right to establish an independent state.
</P>
<P>
Both leaders noted that it would not benefit the peace process
to wrap the interim accords into final status talks.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak has suggested to combine the
Wye accord, which was frozen by former Israeli Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu after finishing the first stage of pull-out,
into the final status talks with the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian side has rejected such proposals.
</P>
<P>
Aznar, who is on a five-day Mideast tour which had already
brought him to Syria, Jordan and Lebanon, will arrive in Tel Aviv
on Thursday to meet Barak. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
