<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkey's secret service has captured another senior
leader of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) abroad and
brought him back to Turkey on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's National Intelligence Agency said in a statement that
Cevat Soysal, codenamed Cemil-Mehmet Hoca, was taken into custody
during a foreign tour.
</P>
<P>
The agency's statement did not say where and when Soysal was
captured. The capture of Soysal dealt a new blow to the Kurdish
rebels after PKK's top leader, Abdullah Ocalan, was captured in
Kenya in February and sentenced to death by Ankara State Security
Court last month. (BC-Turkey-PKK-Leader)
</P>
