FIR rules and harassed the aircraft carrying Mantelis back from
Cyprus to Athens.
</P>
<P>
Greek government spokesman Dimitris Reppas Wednesday also
criticized the Turkish planes' actions, saying that this behavior
was not only military provocation, but a classic political act
with a negative message for the attempted normalization of
relations between the two neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
Relations between Greece and Turkey have been strained over
decades for their disputes in the territorial waters, air space
limits and the delimitation of the continental shelf in the Aegean
Sea, and the Cyprus problem.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, senior officials from the foreign ministries of
Greece and Turkey will meet in Ankara to discuss economic and
cultural cooperation between the two countries in order to improve
the strained relations. 
