other side of the chess board.... We're making a very serious
effort to signal our wish for dialogue and good relations," the
report quoted a British Foreign Office source as saying.
</P>
<P>
Russia's relations with NATO were heavily strained during the
Kosovo conflict. Russia was strongly against NATO's bombing
campaign and canceled all its ties with the military alliance
after the air strikes began. Russia later sent troops into the
Kosovo capital Pristina ahead of NATO, a move that surprised and
exasperated the alliance. 
