<HEADLINE> Cohen to Visit Japan, South Korea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Defense Secretary William Cohen
will take a trip to Japan and South Korea next week, Pentagon
officials said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He will leave Sunday for Tokyo and visit Seoul later in the
week for meetings with senior officials, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
In addition to meeting his Defense Ministry counterparts in
Tokyo, Cohen will meet with the Japanese parliamentary group
involved in developing the Japan-U.S. defense cooperation
guidelines and will discuss the relocation of U.S. military bases
in Okinawa, one of the officials said.
</P>
<P>
In Seoul, Cohen will meet with the commander of U.S. forces on
the peninsula as well as government and defense officials to
discuss diplomatic efforts with China and the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
Cohen will also visit Georgia and Ukraine before returning to
Washington on Aug. 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
