<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0300 GMT, July 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The bodies of John F. Kennedy Jr., his wife and
sister-in-law have been located off the coast of Martha's Vineyard
in Massachusetts State of the United States, days after Kennedy's
plane crashed, government officials announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A dive was under way late Wednesday afternoon to recover the
bodies, the National Transportation Safety Board and the Coast
Guard said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement did not say exactly where the bodies were found,
except that they were at the "wreckage site of a large portion of
the fuselage." (Kennedy-Bodies)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- The Irish Republican Army said Wednesday that
Northern Ireland's 15-month-old Good Friday peace accord had not
delivered tangible progress and it blamed the British government
for the province's political crisis.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to An Phoblact, weekly organ of the IRA's Sinn
Fein political wing, the IRA said current demands for guerrilla
disarmament reflected "the failed agenda which seeks the defeat of
the IRA." (N.Ireland-IRA)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Britain hopes a visit to London by Russian Foreign
Minister Igor Ivanov will mend a rift between the two countries
over NATO's military campaign in Kosovo, British officials said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov, who canceled an earlier visit in May after NATO bombs
struck the Chinese embassy in Belgrade, arrived London Wednesday
and was scheduled to hold talks with Prime Minister Tony Blair
Thursday. (Britain-Russia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak said here Wednesday
that the time was right for his country to achieve peace with all
its Arab neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Barak, speaking after holding talks with British Prime Minister
Tony Blair, said he had appreciated the "positive signs" from
Syria since he took office earlier this month. (Britain-Barak-
Peace)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Defense Secretary William Cohen will take a trip
to Japan and South Korea next week, Pentagon officials said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He will leave Sunday for Tokyo and visit Seoul later in the
week for meetings with senior officials, the officials said. (US-E.
Asia-Cohen) 
</P>
