<HEADLINE> Mongolian Government Dismissed by Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia's Great Hural, or
parliament, voted 41-22 Thursday to dismiss the government of
Prime Minister Janlaviin Narantsatsralt after two days of debate.
</P>
<P>
The Great Hural also decided that acting Minister of External
Relations Nyam-Osorin Tuyaa will act as the new prime minister.
</P>
<P>
The out-going prime minister was pressed to step down after his
private mail to the former First Deputy Prime Minister of Russia,
Yuri Maslyukov, was made public by the parliamentary group of the
Mongolian People's Revolutionary Party (MPRP) one week ago.
</P>
<P>
In that mail, Narantsatsralt reportedly leaked crucial
information about the Erdenet Copper and Molybdenum Mine, a very
important joint venture between Mongolia and Russia, to his
Russian counterpart.
</P>
<P>
The bill to dismiss the government was initiated by 21
lawmakers from the ruling Mongolian Social Democratic Party and
the opposition MPRP who accused Narantsatsralt of bringing
substantial damage to the national interests.
</P>
<P>
Narantsatsralt was appointed Prime Minister on December 9 last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990722.0093 </DOCNO>
