<HEADLINE> Myanmar FM Leaves for ASEAN Ministerial Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar Foreign Minister U Win Aung
left here Thursday for Singapore to attend the 32nd meeting of
foreign ministers of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN) due to begin Friday.
</P>
<P>
Invited by ASEAN Chairman and Singapore Foreign Minister
Shunmugam Jayakumar, U Win Aung will also join the Sixth ASEAN
Regional Forum and the ASEAN Post Ministerial Conference to be
followed, at which ASEAN foreign ministers will hold talks with
their counterparts from 10 dialogue partners including Russia, the
European Union, the United States, China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
The two-day ASEAN ministerial meeting will review ASEAN's
activities and external relations over the past year and lay down
plans for the coming year, according to a recent statement of the
Foreign Ministry of Singapore which is ASEAN's rotating chairman
this year.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for U Win Aung to attend an ASEAN foreign
ministers' meeting since he took office in November last year.
</P>
<P>
At the 31st ASEAN Ministerial Meeting held in Manila in July
last year, attended by former Myanmar foreign minister U Ohn Gyaw,
Myanmar joined in signing the second protocol of the Treaty of
Amity and Cooperation, and the Joint Declaration on A Drug-Free
ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN now groups all ten Southeast Asian countries -- Brunei,
Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the Philippines,
Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
