<HEADLINE> Sensex Pass 4700 Mark in BSE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Sensitive index passed 4700 mark
Thursday on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) following fresh buying
from speculators and sustained purchases by Foreign Institutional
Investors (FIIs).
</P>
<P>
Besides continuous FIIs support, the spurt in activity was also
attributed to speculation that the Reserve Bank of India, the
central bank of the country, was likely to cut interest rates by
half a percent.
</P>
<P>
The BSE sensitive index opened fractionally down at 4656.00 but
later witnessed a rally reflecting the firm trend and closed at
the day's high of 4728.78 as against Wednesday's close of 4659.59.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-100 index rose by 18.28 points to 2047.15 from the
previous close of 2018.87.
</P>
<P>
Dealers anticipated the present rally to continue further till
the Sensex reached the 4868-level which is considered to be the
resistance level.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the Dollex were quoted remarkably up at 467.79
and 180.03 compared with the previous close of 462.22 and 178.66
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
