<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Up Largest Auto Development Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Dongfeng Automobile Company,
based in Shiyan City of central China's Hubei Province, has
succeeded in developing a mini car with complete intellectual
property right, marking the establishment of the country's largest
auto development center.
</P>
<P>
Up to June this year, Dongfeng had developed over 700 types of
automobiles in 19 series, and 26 types of motors in eight series,
which ranked it in the forefront of the development of cargo
vehicle technologies in China.
</P>
<P>
The auto company, established in the late 1960s, has witnessed
a steady development since the introduction of the reform and
opening-up policy nationwide in 1978.
</P>
<P>
The company has all along given top priority to technical
innovation and creation as well as introduction of advanced
foreign technologies, which has finally led the company to success,
a Dongfeng source said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
