<DOCNO> XIE19990722.0103 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Extend Losses on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Share prices extended losses on
the Singapore Stock Market Thursday following falls in Tokyo and
other major regional exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) sank 29.45 points to
close at 2,067.89 points in modest dealings.
</P>
<P>
The volume dropped to 340.23 million shares valued at 514.15
million Singapore dollars (about 302.55 million U.S. dollars).
Losers outpaced gainers by 272 to 59 with 114 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
GoldenAg was the most active stock with 21.34 million units
changing hands. It was followed by AFP which had 19.87 million
shares done. The next was Hotung which had 18.72 million counters
traded.
</P>
<P>
SIA led the gainers of the day running up 40 cents to close at
15.40 Singapore dollars. CityDev edged up 20 cents to finish at
10.90 Singapore dollars. SemLog and Venture moved up 10 cents to
close at 6.00 and 15.00 Singapore dollars respectively while TAC
200 and Thai Pr inched up 10 cents to end at 2.76 and 5.70 U.S.
dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, BMT 100 headed descent incurring a loss of 700
cents to finish at 74.00 Singapore dollars. SPH plunged by 230
cents to close at 30.00 Singapore dollars. SPH retreated 220 cents
to end at 30.20 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers noted the market firmed in early dealings on bargain
hunting but prices later eased following falls in the Tokyo and
other regional bourses.
</P>
<P>
They said cautious sentiment prevailed over the market as
investors waited to see the corporate results to be announced in
the upcoming reporting season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
