<HEADLINE> Karachi Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KARACHI, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Karachi stocks rose marginally
Thursday on rumors that parliament has passed an anti-dumping duty
bill to protect the local fertilizer industry.
</P>
<P>
The 100-share price index rose 8.25 points, or 0.70 percent, to
1186.08 points from Wednesday's 1177.83 points.
</P>
<P>
The market started on a weak note but rumors of passage of
anti-dumping bill caused bullish sentiments and people showed
enthusiasm in buying fertilizer manufacturer stocks, said dealers.
</P>
<P>
The volume on Thursday was recorded at 126.398 million shares
against Wednesday's 160.737 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 172 active issues, gainers managed to beat losers 65
to 58 while 49 remained unchanged. 
