<HEADLINE> Highlights of Today's Diplomatic News </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Following are highlights of
diplomatic news released by Xinhua today:
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Australian Education Minister
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing met here today with visiting
Australian Minister for Education, Training, and Youth Affairs
David Kemp.
</P>
<P>
Both sides exchanged views about promoting educational exchange
and cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Kemp and China's Minister of Education Chen Zhili renewed
earlier today a memorandum of understanding on educational and
training cooperation, in which senior education, professional and
technical education, far-distance education are decided as
priority fields for bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Officials to Discuss Issues on Bilateral Ties
</P>
<P>
Two U.S. senior officials, who are expected to arrive in
Beijing this evening as guest of the U.S. embassy here, will
exchange views with the Chinese side on issues concerning
bilateral ties during their stay in China, said foreign ministry
spokeswoman Zhang Qiyue here today.
</P>
<P>
The two officials are Assistant Secretary of State for East
Asian and Pacific Affairs Stanley Roth and Senior Director for
Asian affairs of the U.S. National Security Council Ken Lieberthal.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
