<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Documents to Promote China's Medical Insurance Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Labor and Social
Security said here today that it has promulgated three new
documents to enhance the supervision of medical services and
effective management of the country's medical insurance funds.
</P>
<P>
The three documents provide more detailed regulations on the
settlement of medical insurance fees for urban employees, the
management of medical services and the payment standards, which
pave the way for the establishment and smooth operation of the
country's medical insurance system.
</P>
<P>
The documents followed three others issued by the government in
May, which deal with designated medical institutions, drug store
management and the scope of medicines for the basic medical
insurance package.
</P>
<P>
To date, 17 provinces across China have formulated overall
plans for the reform of the medical insurance system, and the goal
for the second half of the year is to ensure that the overwhelming
majority of China's provinces draw up similar plans and gradually
implement them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
