<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Carrier Fined for Code of Conduct Infringement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said on
Thursday that it had fined the German airline Lufthansa 10,000
euro (9,524 U.S. dollars) for infringing the European Code of
Conduct for Computer Reservation System.
</P>
<P>
The German carrier was fined for its discriminatory practice of
linking the use of a specific computer reservation system with
incentives that are in contravention to the code.
</P>
<P>
The Computer Reservation System is one that enables travel
agents to book airline tickets. The system contains information
about airline schedules, availability, fares and related services.
</P>
<P>
Most large airlines including Lufthansa have a shareholding in
one of the main Computer Reservation Systems in the world.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Lufthansa introduced incentives linked to the issue of
electronic Lufthansa tickets in Germany and START AMADEUS was the
only Computer Reservation System at the time able to issue
electronic tickets, the incentives therefore could only be earned
by those using the services of the company.
</P>
<P>
The commission said that despite requests, Lufthansa had been
very slow in making its electronic ticketing service available to
other Computer Reservation Systems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990722.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Difference of Car Prices Widens in EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The price gaps for family cars in
the European Union have widened compared with last year, a
European Union survey said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report published by the European Commission and covering
all 15 EU member states said that Britain remained the most
expensive car market in the union while Finland, the Netherlands
and Spain are the least expensive markets.
</P>
<P>
A total of 75 best-selling models of cars were examined for the
report as of May 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
For smaller cars, Peugeot 106 registered the lowest price
difference between the EU member states with 22.0 percent whereas
Renault Clio had the highest difference of 36.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the medium car category, Renault Megane had the smallest
price difference at 26.9 percent while Ford Focus had the largest
difference of 37.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the large car family, Audi A4 had the lowest difference of
17.2 percent while Ford Mondeo the highest difference of 45.3
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990722.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Scholars Refute Lee Teng-hui's Splittist Remarks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Scholars from the Chinese Academy
of Social Sciences (CASS) stressed here today that Lee Teng-hui's
plot to separate Taiwan from China and split China's sovereignty
and territorial integrity is doomed to failure.
</P>
<P>
The scholars said at a forum that Lee has taken a very
dangerous step by stating that cross-straits relations are "state-
to-state", which exposes his true intention of denying the "one
China" principle.
</P>
<P>
They said that Lee's splittist remarks have seriously distorted
historical facts, and are absurdly groundless.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Weidong, a research fellow at the Institute of Taiwan
Studies of CASS, noted that the People's Republic of China has
long been accepted and recognized by the international community
as the sole legal government of China, and naturally has the legal
right to exert sovereignty over Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Yu Heping, a research fellow at the Institute of Modern Chinese
History, said that Taiwan is an inalienable part of China, and
this has been firmly rooted in the minds of the Chinese people
since the very beginning of Chinese history. The ownership of the
island province has long been beyond dispute, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The scholars present at the forum held that Lee has misjudged
the international situation. His evil intention of splitting the
motherland by relying on foreign forces is doomed to failure.
</P>
<P>
They said that Lee's splittist remarks have been strongly
criticized and condemned by the entire Chinese people. The
international community has widely reaffirmed the "one China"
principle.
</P>
<P>
Lee and his followers will become sinners against the Chinese
nation if they do not stop at the brink of the precipice and
immediately return to the "one China" principle, the scholars said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990722.0117 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province Suffering Serious Soil Erosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics show that
soil erosion is becoming increasingly serious in east China's
Zhejiang Province, with more than 17 percent of the province's
land being affected.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Youyu, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
Zhejiang Provincial People's Congress, said today that a total
area of 19,000 sq km is eroded.
</P>
<P>
He said that the province is facing tough challenges from
increasing soil erosion damage, and urged that more attention be
paid to water and soil conservation.
</P>
<P>
He recommended that local leaders be evaluated and promoted
only if they have done a good job of water and soil control.
</P>
<P>
He explained that soil erosion is also one of the factors that
cause local landslides.
</P>
<P>
Last year, local landslides claimed 62 lives in the Lishui area
in the south Zhejiang, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
