<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korea Adheres to "One China" Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 22 (Xinhua) -- South Korea has always respected the
"one China" principle since it established diplomatic relations
with China in August 1992, the Foreign and Trade Ministry said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This position remains unchanged, said the ministry.
</P>
<P>
It voiced concern over the tensions arising recently between
China's mainland and Taiwan after Lee Teng-hui, leader of the
Taiwanese authorities, said that cross-Straits relations should be
defined as "state-to-state, or at least special state-to-state
relations."
</P>
<P>
South Korea hoped that the Taiwan issue can be solved through
dialogue between the two sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
