<HEADLINE> Penny Hardaway, Lakers West Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WEASHINGTON, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Free-agnet guard Penny
Hardaway met with Los Angeles Lakers executive Jerry West recently,
fueling speculation the unrestricted free-agnet guard might be
reunited with former teammate Shaquile O'Neal.
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles Times and Orlando Sentinel reported the team
has considered adding Hardaway, possible through a sign-and-trade
deal with the Orlando Magic.
</P>
<P>
Lakers spokesman John Black confirmed Wednesday that West met
with Hardaway last week, but he wouldn't comment on what was
discussed.
</P>
<P>
"We won't comment on any potential trades or free-agnet
signings as per club policy.
</P>
<P>
The Lakers are over the salary cap, meaning the only way they
could pay Hardaway anything close to market value would be with a
sign-and-trade deal with the Magic.
</P>
<P>
One name mentioned as a possibility in that scenario is Glen
Rice. The Lakers recently picked up their $7 million option on
Rice for next season. 
</P>
