<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taxation Agencies Told to Sever Links With Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China's State Taxation
Administration (STA) has ordered all taxation agencies to sever
their links with government taxation offices, as a measure to wipe
out corruption in the taxation field.
</P>
<P>
The STA said today that taxation agencies set up by or
affiliated to taxation bureaus must cut themselves away from the
latter, by establishing their own independent personnel and
financial systems, and functions.
</P>
<P>
They are also not allowed to contain in their names any word
that might lead people to believe that they have any official
affiliation with state bureaus.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, illegal taxation agencies must be suppressed.
</P>
<P>
The order is intended to halt some agencies soliciting business
in the name of the government.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the STA ordered all taxation agencies who have
offices or desks inside the buildings of taxation bureaus to move
out.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
