<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 70 Youths in Shenzhen Offer to Donate Corneas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- More than 70 young people from
the Shenzhen Energy Group have applied to the Shenzhen Ophthalmic
Hospital to donate their corneas after their deaths, in a bid to
bring sight to more blind people.
</P>
<P>
They were deeply inspired by Xiang Chunmei, a young woman
teacher in this special economic zone, who applied to donate her
corneas when she learned that she was suffering from an incurable
disease. After her death, the corneas she donated restored the
sight of two blind persons.
</P>
<P>
At present, there are donated corneas for only 3,000 of the
three million blind people in China who lost their sight because
of cornea diseases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
