<HEADLINE> End of Monsoon Season to Ease Yangtze Flood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, JULY 22 (Xinhua)-- The monsoon season that has been
hovering over the middle reaches of the Yangtze River is about to
run out of steam, meaning that there will be basically no rain in
the region in the reminder of July, meteorologists say.
</P>
<P>
What used to be drizzles in the monsoon season has turned out
to be heavy rain showers since June 15, bringing serious floods to
the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
So far, three major flood crests have formed in the river, with
the third still moving toward this capital of central China's
Hubei Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
