<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Metallurgical Industry Earns 220 Million Yuan in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China's metallurgical industry
made a profit of 220 million yuan during the first half of this
year, despite sliding prices at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
The sector completed an output value of 99.4 billion yuan
during the half year, up 10.3 percent over the same period of last
year, according to a national meeting on the sector's development
held here today.
</P>
<P>
The industry had a sales revenue of 138.8 billion yuan, down 1.
69 percent on an annual basis, said Pu Haiqing, director of the
State Bureau of the Metallurgical Industry, at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The bureau plans to cut its steel output by ten percent and
earn a profit of five billion yuan this year.
</P>
<P>
During the past six months, prices for major steel products
dropped by 220 yuan per ton from the same period of last year. The
prices are now 50 yuan down from what they were at the beginning
of this year.
</P>
<P>
Pu said that the output reduction has not achieved the original
planned target, but big companies like the Shougang Group and
Shanghai Baoshan steel group have set examples in cutting down
production.
</P>
<P>
The two companies shrank their production during the six-month
period by 9.61 percent and 7.87 percent, respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
