<DOCNO> XIE19990722.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolia's Industrial Output Increases by 2.8 percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Mongolia's industrial output
increased by 2.8 percent in the first half of the year compared
with the same period of last year, but foreign trade dropped by a
big margin, according to official statistics released Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output value amounted to 96.6 billion Tughrik
based on the constant prices of 1995. The output of 60 industrial
products including electricity, thermo-power, oil and refined
copper powder registered increases.
</P>
<P>
The number of sheep increased by 558,400, compared with the
same period of last year, hitting an all-time high.
</P>
<P>
Budgetary revenues increased by 7.2 percent in the first sixth
months of the year.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia's foreign trade in the period under review reached 331.
5 million U.S. dollars, down 10.8 percent from the same period of
last year, with exports amounting to 137.9 million dollars, down 2.
2 percent, and imports amounting to 193.6 million dollars, down 16.
1 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
