<HEADLINE> China's Sci-Tech Audio-Video Program Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Awards were given today to 62
audio and video programs on endangered tigers, harmful drugs,
archaeological discoveries, the environment, biology, and other
science subjects.
</P>
<P>
The biennial prize-giving ceremony is sponsored by the China
Association for Science and Technology and the State Press and
Publication Administration to promote the development of Chinese
audio and video programs on science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The four award categories are the spread of science and
technology, technical training, history of science and important
figures in science, and science reports.
</P>
<P>
There were 131 Chinese audio and video producers and publishers
taking part in the competition, an increase of 48 percent over the
last one.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the overall quality of the programs has greatly
improved, and some of the programs will be shown on TV. 
</P>
</TEXT>
