<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Female Murderers Sentenced to Death in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The First Intermediate People's
Court of Beijing Municipality sentenced two women who had
masterminded the kidnapping and murder of an eight-year-old girl,
to death today.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Xiuqing and Tan Jinfen were farmers in the Mentougou
District, western Beijing. With the help of two accomplices, they
kidnapped Li Xinli, a local primary school girl, on December 18,
1998. They blackmailed Li's family for 150,000 yuan in ransom
money.
</P>
<P>
Zhang and Zheng strangled the girl to death later, after one of
their accomplices, Zheng Xiusheng, was arrested by police on
December 21 last year.
</P>
<P>
Yang Zhaoxiu was today sentenced to life imprisonment, and
deprived of political rights for life. The other accomplice, Zheng
Xiusheng, was sentenced to 15 years imprisonment and deprived of
political rights for three years.
</P>
<P>
According to court investigation, the four also attempted to
abducted an 11-year-old boy in November last year, but failed.
</P>
</TEXT>
