<HEADLINE> Thai Beauty Queens to Work as Tourism Ambassadors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Tourism Authority of Thailand
(TAT) has enlisted a team of beauty queens to work as volunteer
tourism ambassadors, Thailand News Agency reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Paveena Hongsakul, minister of the Prime Minister's Office, was
quoted as saying that the campaign would help improve the
country's image and promote its culture and traditions.
</P>
<P>
