<HEADLINE> China Construction Bank Grants Record Loans in First Half Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China Construction Bank (CCB)
reported today that it had extended a record of more than 1.25
trillion yuan in loans for a half-year period from January to June
this year, which was 78 billion yuan more than at the year's
beginning.
</P>
<P>
A bank spokesman said that, in response to the central
government policy to increase domestic spending, the CCB continued
to grant loans to the sectors of communications, electricity,
telecommunications, and infrastructure, in addition to consumer
credit.
</P>
<P>
More than half of the loan increments went to infrastructure,
while the amount of housing and automobile loans also increased
significantly.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, housing loans to individuals amounted to 35.
7 billion yuan, up 10.7 billion yuan from the beginning of the
year; and consumer loans amounted to 1.08 billion yuan, up 910
million yuan. Deposits for the period also rose to more than 1.59
trillion yuan, up 125.2 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The bank's integrated financial services ability has largely
improved due to the individual consumer credit available in 23
cities and the individual on-line remittance available in 283
cities, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
CCB President Zhou Xiaochuan has asked the bank to pay greater
attention to getting better clients and projects in the second
half while continuing to improve services.  
</P>
</TEXT>
