<HEADLINE> Man Who Killed Taiwanese Woman Given Death Sentence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANSHAN (Liaoning Province), July 22 (Xinhua) -- Yang Rongsong,
of northeast China's Liaoning Province, was given the death
sentence by the Intermediate People's Court of the city of Anshan
and deprived of political rights and fined 15,000 yuan for
homicide, robbery, and kidnapping.
</P>
<P>
Yang and three accomplices were found guilty of illegally
holding and robbing Wei Tein-kang, a Taiwan businessman, and of
killing his girlfriend Lin Ti-chuan.
</P>
<P>
Yang, who was jobless, got the three accomplices, Huang Shidong,
Zhang Shifeng, and Zhao Chuang, to kidnap the two people last July
and handcuffed them and put tape over their mouths, before
injecting them with heroin and torturing them to get money.
</P>
<P>
The two victims were illegally held for more than 30 hours and
robbed of 11,900 yuan worth of cash and property. Lin Ti-chuan
later died of a heroin overdose.
</P>
<P>
Huang was found guilty of homicide and kidnapping and given a
sentence of life in prison and deprived of political rights for
life. Zhao was found guilty of the same crimes and was given a
sentenced of 16 years and deprived of political rights for five
years. Zhang was also sentenced to 15 years and deprived of
political rights for three years for the same crimes.  
</P>
</TEXT>
