<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK to Launch Growth Enterprise Market in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Stock Exchange of Hong Kong
announced a plan Thursday to launch the Growth Enterprise Market (
GEM) in October to offer a venue of business expansion for small
and medium-sized companies.
</P>
<P>
Alec Tsui, chief executive of the Stock Exchange of Hong Kong,
told a news conference here that members of the GEM Listing
Committee will have been appointed by the middle of next month.
</P>
<P>
"GEM will start to accept applications from sponsors once the
Listing Committee is appointed. A sponsor must be registered with
the Securities and Futures Commission as an investment adviser or
securities/exempt dealer," Tsui said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, it must have two experienced principal supervisors
and two experienced assistant supervisors and capital or reserves
of at least 10 million HK dollars (about 1.28 million U.S. dollars)
.
</P>
<P>
"The Exchange expects to announce the first batch of GEM
sponsors in mid-September. Applications for listing are expected
after the sponsor list is published, and the first listing is
expected before the end of the year," Tsui said.
</P>
<P>
K. S. Lo, chairman of the GEM Working Group, stressed that GEM
was of equal standing to the existing stock market, with an
emphasis on growth enterprises.
</P>
<P>
As a separate and an alternative market to the existing stock
market, namely the Main Board, the GEM requires lower listing
qualifications than those of the Main Board.
</P>
<P>
"There will be no profit requirement for listing, and GEM
applicants will only have to show a two-year business history," Lo
explained. "However, the reporting accountant will be required to
report on the financial results for the two years prior to listing.
"
</P>
<P>
He said GEM will be run on the basis of "let the buyer beware."
GEM listing applicants will have to give prominent risk warnings
and investors will be required to sign a risk acknowledgment
statement.
</P>
<P>
Companies incorporated in Hong Kong, China, Bermuda and the
Cayman Islands may apply for listing on GEM. They should have a
focused business and have been under substantially the same
management and ownership for two years.
</P>
<P>
"The minimum public float will be the higher of 30 million HK
dollars or 20 to 25 percent of issued share capital depending on
market demand." Lo said.
</P>
<P>
Underwriting will not be compulsory and the issuer will be free
to decide on the offering mechanism. A minimum of 100 public
shareholders are required. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
