<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Drop 0.38 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks dropped 50.6
points, or 0.38 percent, to close at 13,369.06 Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The market turnover stood at 5.975 billion HK dollars (about
766 million U.S. dollars), 426 million HK dollars (about 54
million U.S. dollars) less than Wednesday's 6.401 billion HK
dollars (about 820 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
While the Finance Counter gained 0.32 percent, Utilities,
Properties and Commerce &AMP; Industry suffered losses of 0.52 percent,
1.13 percent and 0.64 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index went down 2.54 percent
and the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations Index 0.95 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index gained 0.2 points, to open at 13,419.86
Thursday morning and continued the increase to end the morning
session at 13,469.25 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
