<HEADLINE> ASEAN FMs Arrive in Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers from the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) have arrived in
Singapore to attend the regional grouping's annual ministerial
event here.
</P>
<P>
The 32nd ASEAN Ministerial Meeting (AMM), scheduled for Friday
and Saturday, will for the first time bring together all ten
Southeast Asian nations.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN groups Malaysia, Singapore, Brunei, Myanmar, the
Philippines, Thailand, Vietnam, Cambodia, Laos and Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
After Friday morning's opening ceremony, the ministers will
have an informal retreat in the afternoon to discuss among
themselves, without the presence of other officials, issues
related to ASEAN's future and challenges.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first time that a ministerial retreat,
designed under Singapore's current ASEAN chairmanship to encourage
more candid and realistic talks, is incorporated into the AMM.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia's formal entry into the regional grouping this April
finally capped a long-awaited ASEAN wish to hold together all
Southeast Asian countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
