<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN FMs to Review Progress in Regional Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers of the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) will review the
progress in the implementation of a regional plan during their
annual meeting here, ASEAN Secretary-General Rodolfo Severino said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the eve of the 32nd ASEAN Ministerial Meeting (AMM)
to be held here, Severino said the Hanoi Plan of Action (HPA),
adopted at the ASEAN summit in Hanoi last December, will be an
agenda item in the AMM and following related meetings.
</P>
<P>
The HPA is the first in a series of concrete plans mapped out
to realize the Vision 2020, a long-term and broad blueprint for
the region, adopted by ASEAN leaders in 1995.
</P>
<P>
It has a six-year timeframe covering the period from 1999 to
2004. The progress of its implementation is set to be reviewed at
the ASEAN Summit Meetings held every three years.
</P>
<P>
The HPA is "a set of concrete measures intended to place
Southeast Asia's economic recovery on an enduring basis, foster
cooperation and mutual encouragement in financial matters, and
hasten regional economic integration," he said.
</P>
<P>
Severino said ASEAN foreign ministers will meet with their
dialogue partners to focus on how the two sides can cooperate in
carrying out the projects prescribed in the HPA.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN's 10 dialogue partners include the European Union, Japan,
Russia, China and the United States, among others.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers will be preparing for the ASEAN summit
that is taking place in Manila in November, said Severino, adding
that the summit will review the implementation of the HPA and
issue further directives.
</P>
<P>
Following this year's AMM on July 23-24 is the ASEAN Regional
Forum which involves all ASEAN member countries, its 10 dialogue
partners, Mongolia and Papua New Guinea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
