<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigerian Speaker Considers Resignation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Speaker of the House of
Representatives Alhaji Ibrahim Buhari was believed to consider
resignation over the allegations of forgery and perjury levelled
against him.
</P>
<P>
Sources close to him said that he decided to resign after his
party, the People's Democratic Party (PDP), asked him to step
aside to allow for unfettered investigation into the allegations,
according to media reports on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Under the 1999 Constitution, the Speaker is enjoined to forward
his letter of resignation to the Clerk of the House who will
announce that the post of the Speaker is vacant and election will
then be held to fill the position.
</P>
<P>
With the development of Buhari's decision to resign, meetings
were held Wednesday night by legislators preparatory to the
emergence of a new speaker for the House of Representatives.
</P>
<P>
The sources further said that his parents and some PDP elders
had begun serious lobby of the Federal government against
prosecuting the Speaker.
</P>
<P>
Buhari's parents are appealing to the government to see the
Speaker's resignations as enough humiliation, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Speaker Buhari wrote to the House, saying he was
stepping aside until investigations into allegations against him
have been concluded.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, the ruling party to which Buhari belongs said
that "PDP believes that Buhari should step aside from his position
as the Speaker of the House of Representatives, to allow for an
unfettered investigation." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
