<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed lower here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index was nine points lower at 2,195 with a turnover
 of 65 million NZ dollars (34 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the leading stocks, Tranz Rail, which was the biggest
loser Wednesday, recovered 18 cents to 364 cents.
</P>
<P>
Ports of Auckland gained 8 cents to 500 cents and Auckland
Airport 7 to 299 cents,
</P>
<P>
AMP fell 18 cents to 2,085 cents, Fletcher Building 6 to 291
cents while both Fletcher Energy and Carter Holt Harvey shed 5
cents to 565 and 236 cents respectively. Telecom lost 4 cents to
835 cents and Contact Energy and Brierley Investments 1 cent each
to 305 and 52 cents respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
