<HEADLINE> Philippine President to Visit Argentina, Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph Estrada
will visit Argentina and Chile in September upon the invitation of
the leaders of the two countries, presidential spokesman Jerry
Barican said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Estrada has accepted the invitation of Chilean President
Eduardo Frei Ruiz-Tagle and Argentine President Carlos Menem to
visit Santiago and Buenos Aires on September 15-17 and September
18-21 respectively, Barican said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman added that Estrada looks forward to the visit as
an opportunity to strengthen friendly relations with the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
According to Barican, Estrada hopes that his visit to Santiago
"is a manifestation of the importance that Filipinos attach to
their bilateral relations with Chile."
</P>
<P>
The visit to Buenos Aires, on the other hand, will serve "to
reaffirm the strong historic-cultural ties between Argentina and
the Philippines," Barican added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
