<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Construction Bank Reforms Internal Audit System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China Construction Bank (CCB)
announced today that it will have some major reforms of its
internal supervision and audit system.
</P>
<P>
A bank spokesman said that eight auditing sub-divisions will be
set up in Beijing, Shanghai, Nanjing and five other large cities
for a more vertical, efficient internal audit system.
</P>
<P>
It is the first Chinese bank to use this new supervisory and
audit model and bank analysts say that the new model will help
protect the independence of supervisory and audit work.
</P>
<P>
CCB Vice-President Liu Shulan said that the new model will help
solve problems in the traditional audit system under which the
source and outlay of auditors are closely related to those being
audited, thus affecting the independence of the audit work.
</P>
<P>
A detailed plan has been made to implement the new measures,
she said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
