<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-22 09:44 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian Leader Appoints New Chief of Foundation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Iran's paramount leader Ayatollah
Ali Khamenei on Thursday appointed former Defense Minister
Mohammad Forouzandeh as the chairman of the state-run Foundation
of the Oppressed and the Disabled.
</P>
<P>
Forouzandeh is replacing Mohsen Rafiqdoost, who has held the
foundation chairmanship for two five-year tenures, Iran's Islamic
Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In his decree on the appointment, Khamenei expressed hope
that Forouzandeh would make the optimal use of the public assets
of the foundation in serving the disabled war veterans of the
Iran-Iraq war in 1980-88 and the disadvantaged people.
</P>
<P>
Iran set up the foundation after the 1979 Islamic revolution by
taking over the properties of the former Iranian shah regime and
the Iranians who fled Iran. It has become Iran's largest state-run
industrial and commercial group with more than 100 companies in
various fields.
</P>
<P>
Forouzandeh was born in 1953 in Abadan in Iran's southwestern
Khuzestan province. After the Islamic revolution, he was appointed
the director of the province's administrative-political department
and in 1981 as its governor.
</P>
<P>
In 1986, he became chief of the staff of the Islamic
Revolutionary Guards Corp and in 1993 he was appointed by
former President Hashemi Rafsanjani as the defense minister.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
