<HEADLINE> URGENT: WTO Members Approve Leadership Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The ruling General Council of the
World Trade Organization (WTO) on Thursday formally approve a
power-sharing plan to appoint Mike Moore of New Zealand and
Supachai Panithpakdi of Thailand as the WTO's next two consecutive
leaders.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan, Mike Moore of New Zealand is appointed
as Director-General for three years from September 1, 1999 to
August 31, 2002. Supachai Panitchpakdi of Thailand will succeed
Moore from September 1, 2002 for three years to August 31, 2005.
</P>
