<HEADLINE> Preparations Begin for Making Macao SAR Passports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Identification Department of the
Macao government has begun preparations for making passports to be
used by local residents after the establishment of the Macao
Special Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
The Macao Daily News quoted Director Lai Ieng Kit as saying his
department will have to improve relevant technology to prevent
counterfeit passports.
</P>
<P>
Lai noted that the passports would surely be issued after the
founding of the Macao SAR on December 20 this year, but local
residents can submit applications to the department before that
date.
</P>
<P>
As soon as the SAR establishes, the department will exert great
efforts to publicize the passports so that more countries can
accept them and exempt visas, he said. 
</P>
