<HEADLINE> Ajax Beats Revolution 2-1 in Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Shota Arveladze headed home a
corner by Brian Laudrup in the 66th minute as Ajax defeated the
New England Revolution 2-1 in a friendly match in Foxboro,
Massachusetts on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The match was Ajax's debut in the United States. It is now on a
pre-season tour in America.
</P>
<P>
In the 10th minute, Richard Knooper gave a short pass to Greek
international Nikos Machlas. The latter drilled the ball past
Revolution goalkeeper Walter Zenga from five meters out.
</P>
<P>
In the 56th minute, Jamar Beasley leveled the score for the New
England. The 19-year-old forward took Johnny Torres's pass and
slammed the ball past substitute goalkeeper Stanley Menzo from two
meters out by the left post.
</P>
<P>
Only 10 minutes later, Shota Arveladze scored the winner for
Ajax when he headed in a corner kick by Laudrup three meters away
from the left post.
</P>
<P>
Ajax, four-time European champions, finished only sixth in 1998-
1999 season in the Dutch league. 
</P>
</TEXT>
