<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Security Agency Says Iran Training Hamas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Israel's security service Shin
Bet has found that Iran is training members of the Islamic
militant group Hamas, Israel's Haaretz daily reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report said the exclusive training camp is located not far
from the Iranian capital of Tehran and run by Pasdaran Islamic
Revolutionary Guards, which is controlled by Iran's spiritual
leader Ayatollah Khamenei.
</P>
<P>
Shin Bet became aware of the Iranian-Hamas connection several
months ago after it arrested three Hamas members, who admitted
that they had received guerrilla warfare training in Iran, the
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Israel views Iran as a major regional threat to its national
security. Meanwhile, Hamas, which opposes the Israeli-Palestinian
peacemaking, is leading a Palestinian resistance movement against
the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian National Authority stepped up security measures
in the past few months and succeeded in reining in Hamas and other
radical Palestinian groups.
</P>
<P>
But Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak warned recently of fresh
Hamas terror attacks as Israel and the Palestinians resume the
peace process, deadlocked in the past three years under the former
hardline Israeli prime minister, Benjamin Netanyahu. 
</P>
</TEXT>
