<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary At 0930 GMT, July 22 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA -- Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori and his visiting
Brazilian counterpart Fernando Henrique Cardoso signed here
Wednesday the Action Plan of Lima for the promotion of ties
between the South American countries.
</P>
<P>
The Action Plan of Lima provides for the implementation of
actions in short and medium terms in order to strengthen the ties
between the two peoples and governments of the two countries,
which share a 1,500 kilometer-long common border.
</P>
<P>
The document gives special importance to the actions in the
fields of the Amazon area and the common frontier, integration of
transport, environmental protection, anti-drug-traffic and
technological, economic and commercial cooperation.(Peru-Brazil-
Lima Action)
</P>
<P>
---
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton reiterated the one-
China policy on Wednesday as Lee Teng-hui's redefinition of the
cross-strait relationship was refuted on both sides of the straits.
</P>
<P>
"Our policy is clear. We favor the one-China policy. We favor
the cross-strait dialogues," Clinton told a White House press
conference.
</P>
<P>
Clinton said the one-China policy is not a "puzzling fiction."
And although Taiwan and the Chinese mainland are not unified today,
the Chinese take a long view, he added.(US-"One China" Policy)
</P>
<P>
---
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- Latin American countries have reiterated their "One
China" policy, criticizing the recent separatist remarks by Taiwan
's Lee Teng-hui.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian Foreign Ministry spokesman, Marcos Galvao said
that Brazil has been recognizing the government of People's
Republic of China as the only legitimate one representing the
whole China ever since the establishment of diplomatic relations
with China in 1974.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan government on Wednesday also reaffirmed its
position that there exists only one China, which is the People's
Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
Chile's Foreign Minister Juan Gabriel Valdes on Wednesday told
Xinhua that Chile maintains its clear policy toward China,
recognizing only the People's Republic of China. (Latin America-"
One China " Policy)
</P>
<P>
---
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. House of Representatives voted Wednesday
to pay for strengthening security at U.S. embassies around the
world one year after the bomb attacks on two U.S. embassies in
Africa.
</P>
<P>
The bill, passed easily by a voice vote, authorized 1.4 billion
U.S. dollars to protect U.S. diplomatic missions from the threat
of international terrorism.
</P>
<P>
The bill noted that security at half the 250 U.S. facilities
abroad is considered inadequate. (US-Embassy Security)
</P>
<P>
---
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Bad weather prevented U.S. space shuttle Columbia
from blasting off early Thursday morning in Cape Canaveral,
Florida State, with Eileen Collins, the first woman to lead a U.S.
space flight.
</P>
<P>
After aborting the first scheduled launch with six seconds
remaining just after midnight Tuesday because of a faulty sensor,
launch controllers were forced to scrub it again early Thursday
when a lightning storm moved into the area.
</P>
<P>
NASA said it would try again early Friday. (US-Space Shuttle-
Abortion) 
</P>
</TEXT>
