<HEADLINE> Road Accident Claims 15 in W. Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen people were killed in west
Kenya Wednesday evening in a road accident involving two
privately-owned buses, the East African Standard newspaper
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ten other passengers were seriously injured in the accident in
Kakamega district of Kenya's Western Province.
</P>
<P>
Eye witnesses said the accident occurred after the bus collided
 head-on with another mini-bus (known as matatu in Kenya). The
bloody scene of the accident was littered with human flesh as
many bodies were mutilated beyond recognition.
</P>
<P>
Provincial traffic police boss Justus Mwangi said the accident
was a result of careless driving.
</P>
<P>
Matatus are infamous for its speeding and careless driving,
which have caused a great deal of accidents in Kenya. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
