<HEADLINE> Philippines: Total Manufacturing Up, Net Sales Down in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines on Thursday posted
a year-on-year increase of 2.4 percent in its total manufacturing
and a decline of 4.4 percent in the net sales volume in May.
</P>
<P>
According to the results of a monthly survey of selected
industries released by the National Statistics Office, the 2.4
percent growth of production volume decelerated from 4.2 percent
in April.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the 4.4 percent decrease in the net sales
volume came after an increase of 1.4 percent in April.
</P>
<P>
Food manufacturing, rubber products, chemicals and transport
equipment turned in positive performance in both production and
sales.
</P>
<P>
However, non-metallic mineral products and paper and paper
products, electrical machinery, wood and wood products, furniture
and fixtures, wearing apparel, beverage and tobacco posted
decreases in both.
</P>
<P>
In May 1999, the value of production index of 476.1 increased
by 4.7 percent from 454.7 in May 1998 while the volume of
production index increased by 2.4 percent to 138.1 from 134.9 last
year.
</P>
<P>
The value of net sales for May 1999 decreased by 1.3 percent
compared to last year while the volume of net sales posted a
decrease of 4.4 percent over last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
