<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mobile Phone Network Upgraded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China today increased its cellular
phone number digits to 11 from the previous 10, expanding its
network capacity by 10-fold, according to the Ministry of
Information Industry (MII).
</P>
<P>
This is the largest mobile phone network upgrade in the world,
and also the first time China has increased phone numbers
nationwide.
</P>
<P>
By upgrading, the country's mobile phone network is now able to
serve 250 million to 280 million users, said an official of the
MII.
</P>
<P>
Beginning today, all existing cellular phone numbers will have
a "0" inserted between their third and fourth digits. All current
phone operations and functions will otherwise remain unchanged,
said the MII official, adding that the upgrading will not affect
international roaming operations.
</P>
<P>
The number of cellular phone users in China has snowballed
during the past decade. For example, the number of China Telecom
users has increased on average by 70 percent annually since it
started the service in 1987.
</P>
<P>
With some 28 million users so far, China boasts the third
largest cellular phone network after the United States and Japan.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
