<HEADLINE> India's Garment Exports up 18 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Exports of garments from India
registered an 18 percent growth in U.S. dollar terms in the first
half of the current year, according to the Clothing Manufactures
Association of India (CMAI).
</P>
<P>
In a press release issued Thursday, CMAI President Premal Udani
said exports of garments during this period touched 2.7 billion
U.S. dollar mark.
</P>
<P>
India's garment exports are likely to cross five billion dollar
mark by December 1999 on the back of the healthy 18 percent
increase in exports over the last six months, Mr. Udani said.
</P>
<P>
"Despite the South-East Asian economic crisis and the trouble
across India's frontiers, the garment exports from India will
notch up 5.6 billion U.S. dollars," he added. 
