<HEADLINE> Siemens to Set up More Subsidiaries, Offices in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Siemens Ltd. China (SLC) will
open subsidiaries and representative offices in the cities of
Hangzhou, Nanjing, Xiamen, Nanchang, Guiyang, Nanning and, Urumqi
in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Ernst Berens, the president of SLC, said he hopes his company's
annual business volume in China will exceed its annual turnover of
eight billion Deutsche Marks (4.14 billion US dollars) in the
United States within ten years.
</P>
<P>
Berens made the remark last week while attending a ceremony
marking the opening of a new representative office in Changsha,
capital of central China's Hunan Province. Siemens' annual volume
of business in China stands at four billion Deutsche Marks,
accounting for 30 percent of the firm's total business volume in
the Asian-Pacific Region.
</P>
<P>
As one of the world's major electrical engineering and
electronics companies, Siemens' business operation in China began
as early as 127 years ago.
</P>
<P>
It now has established 12 solely funded businesses and 44 joint
ventures in China, with 26,000 employees engaging in seven
distinct sectors. The Changsha representative office is the
twenty-third of its kind in China.  
</P>
