<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Customs have seized
57 kilograms of 17th century Dutch coins that were being attempted
to be smuggled to Singapore, press reports said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The coins were seized by the Customs recently when a man from
Puttalam in Sri Lanka's northwest attempted to smuggle them on a
flight to Singapore, the Daily News said.
</P>
<P>
The Archaeological Department has confirmed that these coins
belong to the 17th century.
</P>
<P>
