<HEADLINE> Puerto Ricans Avoid Clash with U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Jose Ortiz scored 23 points,
including the final seven in the last 95 seconds, to lift Puerto
Rico a 80-75 triumph over Canada in Olympic men's basketball
qualifying match in San Juan, Puerto Rico, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The triumph means that Puerto Rico, 5-1 in round-robin play,
will be able to qualify for the Tournament of Americas in at least
the third place and avoid joining the path with the United States.
</P>
<P>
Steve Nash of the NBA Dallas Mavericks gave Canada a 73-70 lead
on a three-point basket with 2:30 to play, but Ortiz, who would
not be denied in the final minutes, finished with 11 rebounds in
addition to game high scoring honors.
</P>
<P>
Rowan Barret led Canada with 17 points and Todd MacCullouch
added 16.
</P>
<P>
Puerto Rico faces an almost certain defeat in Thursday's final
game of round-robin play and could be equaled at 5-2 by Canada and
Argentina if they win Thursday. But tie-breaker rules would not
allow both to move ahead of them in the standings and send them
against the US team.
</P>
<P>
A loss here Wednesday to Canada would have ensured the
Tournament of the Americas hosts a date Saturday against the US
National Basketball Association stars unless they managed to upset
them two days earlier.
</P>
<P>
The Canadians fell to 4-2 but still control their own fate. A
victory over Venezuela on Thursday will give them no worse than
third place. A loss could drop them into the path of the "Dream
Team."
</P>
<P>
Venezuela must beat Canada by 16 points to play for an Olympic
berth Saturday and must defeat Canada by 42 and have Argentina
lose to advance and avoid the US team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
