<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB, World Bank to Discuss Asian Social Policy Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
and the World Bank will jointly hold a 4-day forum on Asian social
policy issues here starting from October 26, the ADB said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
About 200 senior representatives from Asian governments and
civil society, the donor community, the private sector and both
banks will attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The key topics to be addressed include long term social
developments for Asia; targeting social expenditures and reforming
social sectors; social safety protection and other social
programs.
</P>
<P>
During the forum, the ADB will also discuss its new poverty
relief strategy, which is due to be considered by the ADB Board of
Directors in November.
</P>
<P>
The forum, which aims to draw operational lessons for social
policy from the experience of the 1997-1999 Asian crisis, follows
the January 1999 ADB social policy meeting in Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
The forum is said to be part of a series of events to promote
sustainable social policy for Asia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
