<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Airforce Kills 85 Tamil Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 22 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan airforce had killed
85 Tamil rebels and wounded another 105 in a bombing of the
rebels-held jungles in the east of the country early in the week,
military sources said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
These figures have been confirmed by intercepted radio messages
of the rebels, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Among the dead are reportedly several top ranking rebel
military leaders.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that on Monday MI-24 helicopter gunships and
Siai Marchetti ground attack aircraft had been used by the
airforce which later used an Israeli-built Kfir bomber as well.
</P>
<P>
Several rebel vehicles including one with a full load of rebels
were also destroyed in the attack.
</P>
<P>
Tamil rebels have been waging a 16-year separatist war against
the government to demand a homeland for Tamil minorities in the
northern and eastern Sri Lanka. 
</P>
</TEXT>
