<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's SEA Games Team Inaugurated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's National Sports
Council (KONI) Chairman Wismoyo Arismunandar Wednesday inaugurated
the 20th Southeast Asian (SEA) Games contingent at the Senayan
Indoor Tennis Stadium here, The Jakarta Post reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The contingent consists of 238 male and 112 female athletes
from 20 sports, 162 coaches and 82 officials. They will leave the
country on August 3 using national carrier Garuda Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
KONI's official in charge of athlete development Mochammad
Hindarto said that of 235 events to be featured at Bandar Seri
Begawan from August 7 to 15, Indonesia would not compete in 36
events: 19 events in the track and field, one hockey event, eight
shooting events, two squash and six lawn bowls events.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Wismoyo urged athletes to contribute their best
to the country in order to retain the overall title.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian Taekwondo Association has a target of three
golds in the SEA Games. But the association secretary-general
Ahmad Zarkasih Hamid was optimistic that the national taekwodoins
would be able to win three golds in the men's sector and two in
the women's sector.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian Table Tennis Association has set its sight on
two of the seven golds on offer in the Games. The association's
official R.M.Noeryanto said the country's strongest chances for
gold were in the men's doubles and team events.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian Tennis Association has targeted three golds. Two
years ago, national players won golds in the women's singles,
doubles and team event and men's doubles and team.
</P>
<P>
The Indonesian Basketball Association Chairman Sutiyoso
expressed hope that the national team could grab the silver medal
in the Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
