<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Huge Boa Constrictors Found in Yunnan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- Two large boa constrictors have
been found at the Yuantong Temple, in the suburbs of this capital
of southwest China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
They were 3.5 m and four m long, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The smaller one, which weighs more than 40 kg, was seen
swimming in a pool in the temple on July 10 this year, and the
other, weighing 60 kg, was seen in the same pool four days later.
</P>
<P>
Local people affirmed that such snakes are rare in the district.
</P>
<P>
The temple, first built more than 1,000 years ago and rebuilt
about 300 years ago, is the largest in the Kunming area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
