<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Venezuela Seizes 1.6 Tons of Marihuana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan anti-narcotic
authorities have seized 1.6 tons of marihuana hidden in a boat in
a village on the Margarita Island of the country, a newspaper
reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This is the third time that the National Guard has seized over
one ton of drugs this year, chief of the coast guard Luis Felipe
Montilla was quoted by el Nacional daily as reporting.
</P>
<P>
Montilla said the boat, which came from Maracaibo, might
transport drugs from Colombia and smuggle them to Europe and the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Margarita Island is used by drug cartels as a transfer point
since it has 325 kilometers of coast lines, which make the control
of boats difficult, said the Venezuelan Authorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
