<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peru, Brazil Sign Lima Action Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori
and his visiting Brazilian counterpart Fernando Henrique Cardoso
signed here Wednesday the Action Plan of Lima for the promotion of
ties between the South American countries.
</P>
<P>
President Cardoso arrived here on Tuesday night on a two-day
visit to Peru.
</P>
<P>
The Action Plan of Lima provides for the implementation of
actions in short and medium terms in order to strengthen the ties
between the two peoples and governments of the two countries,
which share a 1,500 kilometer-long common border.
</P>
<P>
The document gives special importance to the actions in the
fields of the Amazon area and the common frontier, integration of
transport, environmental protection, anti-drug-traffic and
technological, economic and commercial cooperation
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Peru's Foreign Minister Fernando de
Trazegnies and his Brazil's counterpart Luis Felip Lampreia signed
several accords, such as the ones for the creation of a frontier
committee and for judicial cooperation between diplomatic
academies of the two counties.
</P>
<P>
Peru-Brazil trade has reached some 600 million dollars a year
on the average. But the two neighboring counties hoped the volume
would reach more than one billion dollars in the forthcoming years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
