<HEADLINE> Berizzo Signs with Marseille </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Argentine international Eduardo
Berizzo completed a 20-million francs (3.3 million U.S. dollars)
transfer from River Plate to Olympique Marseille in Marseille,
France, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"I want to become champion of France and Europe," the central
defender who won three Argentine titles with River Plate was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old Berizzo, who began his career at Newell's Old
Boys and spent two years in Mexico playing for Atlas in the mid-
1990s, signed on a three-year contract as replacement for France's
World Cup libero Laurent Blanc. 
</P>
