<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Survey Says Real Income Falls in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The real income of Venezuelans
fell by 3.84 percent over the first six months of the year with
the country's rising unemployment and sluggish economy, the
Datanalisis research group said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the group's survey, the consumption of foods fell
by 7.9 percent, that of rice, flour and pasta fell by between 12
and 13 percent, and that of meat, cheese and milk fell by more
than 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
Supermarket chains registered a fall of 20 percent in sales in
the first half of the year.
</P>
<P>
The official jobless figure stood at 15.9 percent in Venezuela.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990722.0307 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. to Set Up Anti-Drug Center in Ecuador </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, July 21 (Xinhua) -- The United States and Ecuador have
completed the first phase of an agreement on the establishment of
an anti-narcotics center in a military base in northeastern
Ecuador, the Ecuadorian military authorities said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A P3 Orion plane of the U.S. air force will land constantly at
the Manta base, in the province of Manabi, and in the future,
another two planes will be added to the electronic vigilance or
counter-measures, the authorities said.
</P>
<P>
During his recent visit to Ecuador, Charles Wilhelm, chief of
the U.S. South Command, inspected the runway and parking area, in
addition to the elimination of undergrowth at the head of the take-
off platform and runway of the base.
</P>
<P>
An office for the installation of U.S. computers and
communication equipment has already been built on the base.
</P>
<P>
If the United States reaches an accord with the Ecuadorian
authorities, it plans to invest between 20 and 40 million dollars
in improvements to the base, thus permitting the landing and take-
off of radar planes and fuel supply aircraft.
</P>
<P>
An official from the U.S. air force will be resident at the
base to work alongside his Ecuadorian counterpart for the
coordination of planes and to perform the necessary logistical
actions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
