<HEADLINE> Publication of Biographical Studies Underway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 22 (Xinhua) -- China is set to complete the
publication of a series of critical biographies, 200 books in all
by the year 2003, which will present an objective appraisal of
more than 270 of the country's outstanding historical figures, of
all nationalities and from all walks of life.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest such project ever undertaken in the country,
as it promises to be a comprehensive study and overall review of
China's traditional thought and culture.
</P>
<P>
The book series are being published by Nanjing University
Publishing House. So far, 102 books in the series have been
published. 
</P>
</TEXT>
