<HEADLINE> Rios Staggers to Win over Unseeded Gumy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, July 21 (Xinhua) -- Chile's Marcelos Rios held off a
tough challenge against unseeded Argentine Hernan Gumy, needing
three sets to enter the third round of the Mercedes Cup in
Stuttgart, Germany, on Wednesday,
</P>
<P>
Rios, seeded third in the claycourt event, lost the first set
on a tie break and then won a close tiebreak to take the second.
His opponent faded in the third and the Chilean won 6-7, 7-6, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
Rios will next play unseeded German Jens Knippschild who surged
from 5-2 down in the first set to beat Argentine Mariano Zabaleta
7-6, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Gustavo Kuerten, No. 5 on the ATP rankings, pulled out
after just 37 minutes of his opening match when he led Swede Mague
Norman 5-2.
</P>
<P>
The 1997 French Open champion, reigning champion in Stuttgart,
said he was exhausted after playing three matches in Brazil's 3-2
defeat by France in a Davis Cup quarter-final tie at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
Local favorite Tommy Haas, seeded seventh, beat Argentine
Mariano Puerta with straight set victory 7-5, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Haas will go on to meet Norway's Christian Ruud, who knocked
out Swede Thomas Johansson, seeded ninth, with a straightforward 6-
2, 6-2 win.
</P>
<P>
The fifth seed Alber Corretja of Spain had no trouble to knock
off Rainer Schuettler of Germany 6-2, 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
